Table A: Running EQ6 from EQ3/6-V8.0a (R43a) for PC
Description= 'Fresh water-brine mixing; PHRQPITZ test problem 5c'
This is part of the EQ3/6 Test Case Library
Add the calcite saturated fresh water defined on the EQ3NR test input file
calnacl.3i to the calcite saturated brine defined by the EQ6 test case
calhal.6i. The fresh water is treated as a special reactant; whose
composition was taken from the pickup file generated by running calnacl.3i.
Saturation with calcite is to be maintained; but the log pCO2 is allowed to
drift. The starting calcite-saturated brine system from calhal.6i contains
calcite; halite; and fix_CO2(g). These minerals (two real; one fictive) are
removed when the run begins (some calcite is put back as a reactant; see
below). Because a fixed fugacity option for CO2(g) is not specified; the
